item.title: Why Use Magellan
item.dc:creator: JohnDee
item.content:encoded:
You Run Your Business

Let Magellan Find the Money

Magellan Capital has been assisting growth stage companies raise capital since 1980. The obstacles faced by many small companies in raising capital is substantial, and many times, unobtainable. Most stock offerings by growth stage companies fail because they donât provide an exit strategy for investors. If a company is unable to show an investor how to get his money out, it's not going in. Companies can provide investors an exit strategy by completing a Reverse Merger and offering shares in a publicly traded company or to conduct a Mini-IPO. Magellan provides clean shells used for Reverse Mergers to take companies public. Magellan owns the shells we provide and has completed their clean-up and reorganization. We also bring together securities lawyers, auditors, marketers, and stock brokers, to raise money through PIPES or Mini-IPOâs. Magellan, and its affiliated companies have substantial the experience with serving growth stage companies. The following is a list of our achievements.
  • Developed, sold, or brokered over 160 public shell companies.
  • Completed over 100 domestic reverse mergers and 38 cross border transactions
  • Financial backer of 6 securities brokerage/dealers
  • Market maker in over 300 small cap companies
  • Offices in the US, Switzerland, and China to raise capital for growth stage companies.
  • Owned broker/dealer with 8 offices and 243 stockbrokers
  • Underwrote 64 public offerings and over 300 private placements
  • First Reverse Mergers between US and European companies. French, Swiss, Spanish, German, Italian, and the UK.
  • Partner in Private Swiss bank
  • First Reverse Merger between US and Chinese company
  • Worked with Chinese government to open up Chinese Reverse Mergers
  • Assisted in establishing the Shenzhen Stock Exchange and listing Chinese companies
  • Advisor to 6 major US investment banks in complete their US/China Reverse Mergers.
  • Advisor to many US banks and institutions on China investment.
